'''Target surplus''' represents the amount of additional capital held by a financial institution beyond the [[Bank regulation|regulatory requirements]] in order to ensure that the chances of breaching [[Capital requirement|capital adequacy]] or solvency requirements are significantly reduced.

Adelphi University graduate Chris Nocera is often credited with first implementing it into economic behavioral analytics. 

