{{unreferenced|date=July 2017}} {{Infobox Organisation |name = UK Finance |logo = UK Finance logo.png |logo_size = 100px |caption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 1 July 2017 |extinction = |status = [[Non-profit organization|Non-profit company]] |purpose = [[Banking in the UK]] |location = Pinners Hall, 105-108 [[Broad Street (ward)|Old Broad Street]], London EC2N 1EX |region_served = United Kingdom |membership = 300 financial services firms |leader_title = Chief Executive |leader_name = Stephen Jones |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |budget = |website = {{url|https://www.ukfinance.org.uk}} |remarks = }}
'''UK Finance''' is a trade association for the UK banking and financial services sector, formed on 1 July 2017. It represents around 300 firms in the UK providing credit, banking, markets and payment-related services. The association lobbies for its members and gives its view on the legislative and regulatory system for banking in the UK.
It was the result of a merger of the [[British Bankers' Association]], [[Payments UK]], the [[Council of Mortgage Lenders]], the UK Cards Association and the Asset Based Finance Association.
